[normal]Additional
[normal] Benefits
[normal]As well as 
[normal]deliver
[normal]ing
[normal] significant
[normal] cashable savings there are other 
[normal]benefits 
[normal]that come from a 
[normal]national, collaborative framework established ‘by the sector, for the sector’
[normal]:
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Reduc
[normal]ing
[normal] duplication of effort involved in running separate OJEU procurement processes
[normal], all timely and costly administration processes
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Improv
[normal]ing
[normal] control and safeguarding and increas
[normal]ing
[normal] provision and transparency of management information to enable visibility over working practices and a strategic view of 
[normal]expenditure
[normal] 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Encourag
[normal]ing
[normal] supply chains to engage with the SME community recognising Government’s desire to see SMEs and local businesses play a significant role in public sector service delivery
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Easy, efficient and swift temporary workers recruitment process 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Enabl
[normal]ing
[normal] sharing of commercial knowledge, including supplier and market intelligence and expert advice and facilitat
[normal]ing
[normal] strategic relationships with suppliers to gain better VFM, improve performance and align with organisational priorities and government agendas, developing the sector and supply market.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Improved demand management and temporary/permanent workforce planning through far enhanced provision of management information.
